[1mRecipe 9.10: Multi-Modal Imaging Fusion and Analysis[22m covers:[0m[0m
[0m[0m
- **The Problem:** Clinicians mentally fusing CT, MRI, PET, and other modalities for treatment planning, with real-world scenarios in radiation oncology, neurosurgery, and cardiology[0m[0m
- **The Technology:** Deep explanation of image registration (rigid and deformable), mutual information metrics, deep learning registration networks, uncertainty quantification, and why multi-modal fusion is fundamentally hard (different physics, temporal mismatch, organ motion, no ground truth)[0m[0m
- **General Architecture:** Modality-agnostic pipeline from ingestion through preprocessing, registration, fusion, analysis, and clinical integration[0m[0m
- **AWS Implementation:** SageMaker (registration models), S3 (image storage), Step Functions (orchestration), DynamoDB (metadata), Lambda (lightweight tasks), HealthLake (DICOM store), EC2 GPU (clinical review)[0m[0m
- **6-step pseudocode walkthrough:** Study matching, preprocessing, rigid registration, deformable registration, fusion product creation, QA review[0m[0m
- **Honest Take:** Practical insights on when rigid is sufficient, DICOM plumbing headaches, uncertainty quantification as the future[0m[0m
- **Variations:** Real-time intraoperative fusion, longitudinal response assessment, AI-assisted contour propagation[0m[0m
- **All required sections** per RECIPE-GUIDE.md including prerequisites table, ingredients, expected results with benchmarks, related recipes, resources, implementation timeline, and tags[0m[0m
